text: The House at 379 West State Street is a historic Queen Anne revival style house in Trenton, New Jersey. It was added to the National Register of Historic Places on January 23, 1980. It currently houses the African American Chamber of Commerce of New Jersey branch., African American Chamber of Commerce of NJ. ==See also== *National Register of Historic Places listings in Mercer County, New Jersey ==References== Category:Houses on the National Register of Historic Places in New Jersey Category:Federal architecture in New Jersey Category:Houses in Trenton, New Jersey Category:National Register of Historic Places in Trenton, New Jersey Category:Queen Anne architecture in New Jersey Category:New Jersey Register of Historic Places
